quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  10,26,"To those who do what is good, (is granted) goodness and increase! Neither does darkness nor abasement cover their faces! Such are Companions of the Garden (Paradise); they will dwell therein"
  10,27,"But, as for those who have earned ill, the reward of evil is the like thereof; abasement (ignominy) shall cover them - They shall have none to protect them against Allah - as though their faces were veiled with the deep darkness of the night. Such are the"
  10,28,"And on the day when We gather them all together, then We will say to those who associated other gods (with Us), \"To your places, you and your associates!\" and We will separate them; and their associates will say, \"It was not us you worshipp"
  10,29,"But Allah is witness enough between us and you, that we were unaware of your worship"
  10,30,"There shall every soul experience what it did (or has sent on) before; and they shall be returned unto Allah, their rightful Lord, and that which they used to invent shall fail them"
  10,31,"Say, \"Who provides you from the heaven and the earth? Who has power over hearing and sight? And who brings forth the living from the dead, and brings forth the dead from the living? And who governs all affairs (or regulates, directs the course of eve)"
  10,32,"Such, then, is Allah, your true Lord! What is there after the truth but error? How then can you turn away"
  10,33,"Thus is the Word of your Lord justified against those who commit abomination (or rebel) - verily, they believe not"